gdcSc5000MIBVersion.name: gdcSc5000MIBVersion
gdcSc5000MIBVersion.description: The version number of the MIB, to allow products to know which MIB is being supported. The version number will be x.yzT where x is a major revision (1-9), y is a minor revision(0-9), z is a typo revision (0-9) and T indicates the MIB is still a test revision(A-Z). When a release is complete no T should exist.

gdcSc5000TimingTable.name: gdcSc5000TimingTable
gdcSc5000TimingTable.description: A table that contains information about the source of shelf timing in the system.

gdcSc5000TimingEntry.name: gdcSc5000TimingEntry
gdcSc5000TimingEntry.description: A list of information for each node in the system.

gdcSc5000TimingIndex.name: gdcSc5000TimingIndex
gdcSc5000TimingIndex.description: The value indicates the node number for which this entry contains management information. The gdcSc5000TimingIndex is based off of the IFindex in MIB-II. The gdcSc5000TimingIndex value is used to indicate the slot, line and drop of the node in the SCM shelf that is being addressed. The index is defined as: ssllddii. where ss is from 1-32, ll is 1,dd is 0 and ii is 0.

gdcSc5000SrcShelfTiming.name: gdcSc5000SrcShelfTiming
gdcSc5000SrcShelfTiming.description: Identifies which unit or units are the source of shelf timing defined as follows: If one unit is defined as fourMegClk(2) then only one other unit may be defined as eightKiloClk(3) and the remaining units must be defined as inhibit(1). If one unit is defined as eightKiloClk(3) then only one other unit may be defined as fourMegClk(2) and the remaining units must be defined as inhibit(1). If one unit is defined as fourMegAnd8kClk(4) then the remaining units must be defined as inhibit(1).

sc5000ShelfNodeTypes.name: sc5000ShelfNodeTypes
sc5000ShelfNodeTypes.description: Each octet contains the Node Type of the card occupying the slot. Values are as follows: empty 0 vf288 1 sc5001 2 sc5520 3 datx2011 4 sc700G2 6 sc700G3 7 sc616 12 sc702G2 15 sc5034 17 scdualV34 18 sc613 19 sc5553 20 sc611 21 sc710d2 23 sc700grRP 24 sc710d2RP 26 mp7002 29 uas7616 30 scm 31 sc521 32 sc5002 33

sc5000ShelfAdminStatus.name: sc5000ShelfAdminStatus
sc5000ShelfAdminStatus.description: Each octet xx contains the Admin Statuses of the Network Elements(NEs) occupying slot xx. Each octet is bitmapped as follows: bit 7:\ bit 6: Admin Status of NE in slot xx, line 4 bit 5:\ bit 4: Admin Status of NE in slot xx, line 3 bit 3:\ bit 2: Admin Status of NE in slot xx, line 2 bit 1:\ bit 0: Admin Status of NE in slot xx, line 1 Values per pair of bits are: 01 Up 10 Down 00 No NE present

sc5000ShelfOperStatus.name: sc5000ShelfOperStatus
sc5000ShelfOperStatus.description: Each octet xx contains the Operational Statuses of the Network Elements(NEs) occupying slot xx. Each octet is bitmapped as follows: bit 7:\ bit 6: Oper Status of NE in slot xx, line 4 bit 5:\ bit 4: Oper Status of NE in slot xx, line 3 bit 3:\ bit 2: Oper Status of NE in slot xx, line 2 bit 1:\ bit 0: Oper Status of NE in slot xx, line 1 Values per pair of bits are: 01 Up 10 Down 00 No NE present

sc5000ShelfClockProvider.name: sc5000ShelfClockProvider
sc5000ShelfClockProvider.description: Octet 1 contains the slot number of the card providing the 4MHz clock. Octet 2 contains the line number of the card providing the 4MHz clock. Octet 3 contains the slot number of the card providing the 8kHz clock. Octet 4 contains the line number of the card providing the 8kHz clock. A value of 0 indicates that no card is providing the clock.

sc5000ShelfLTUHwayAssgn.name: sc5000ShelfLTUHwayAssgn
sc5000ShelfLTUHwayAssgn.description: Octet 1 contains the slot number of the LTU responsible for Highway 1. Octet 2 contains the slot number of the LTU responsible for Highway 2. Octet 3 contains the slot number of the LTU responsible for Highway 3. Octet 4 contains the slot number of the LTU responsible for Highway 4. If Highway x does not have an LTU then the value in Octet x is 00.

sc5000ShelfClockMode.name: sc5000ShelfClockMode
sc5000ShelfClockMode.description: Indicates which LTU is supplying the clocks, LTU designated as the primary or fallback. none(3) will only occur when the SCM determines that neither of the cards assigned to be the clock provider exists.

sc5000ShelfClocks.name: sc5000ShelfClocks
sc5000ShelfClocks.description: Octet 1 contains the slot number of the primary LTU responsible for providing the shelf clock. Octet 2 contains the line number of the primary LTU responsible for providing the shelf clock. Octet 3 contains the primary timing source. Values are internal (1), network (2), external (3), cascade (4), and station (5). Octet 4 contains the slot number of the DSE responsible for providing the external timing source to the primary LTU. Octet 5 contains the line number of the DSE responsible for providing the external timing source to the primary LTU. Octet 6 contains the slot number of the fallback LTU responsible for providing the shelf clock. Octet 7 contains the line number of the fallback LTU responsible for providing the shelf clock. Octet 8 contains the fallback timing source. Values are internal (1), network (2), cascade (4), and station (5).

sc5000ShelfAutoClockRevert.name: sc5000ShelfAutoClockRevert
sc5000ShelfAutoClockRevert.description: enable(1) indicates that the SCM will allow the primary LTU to resume providing the system timing.

sc5000ShelfRevertToPrimaryClk.name: sc5000ShelfRevertToPrimaryClk
sc5000ShelfRevertToPrimaryClk.description: execute(2) forces the primary LTU to resume providing the system timing.

sc5000HighwayTable.name: sc5000HighwayTable
sc5000HighwayTable.description: A table that contains information about Highway and Time Slot allocation.

sc5000HighwayEntry.name: sc5000HighwayEntry
sc5000HighwayEntry.description: A list of information for each highway.

sc5000HighwayNumber.name: sc5000HighwayNumber
sc5000HighwayNumber.description: The value indicates the highway to be configured.

sc5000HighwayAllocation.name: sc5000HighwayAllocation
sc5000HighwayAllocation.description: There are 3 Octets per Time Slot. Octets 1,2,3 are representative of Time Slot 1, Octets 4,5,6 are representative of Time Slot 2, etc. In each grouping, the first octet indicates the shelf slot (1-32) to which the time slot has been assigned. The second octet indicates the line (1-4) to which the time slot has been assigned. The third octet defines the allocation for the time slot. The values are as follows: 1 = available 2 = not available 3 = Private Line (DSE Data) 4 = SN/Restoral (DBU data) If a time slot has not been assigned then the grouping is 00:00:01

sc5000LTUConfigTable.name: sc5000LTUConfigTable
sc5000LTUConfigTable.description: A table that contains information about the configuration of the LTUs in the shelf.

sc5000LTUConfigEntry.name: sc5000LTUConfigEntry
sc5000LTUConfigEntry.description: A list of information for each LTU in the shelf.

sc5000SlotNumber.name: sc5000SlotNumber
sc5000SlotNumber.description: The value indicates shelf slot containing the LTU.

sc5000DS0Assign.name: sc5000DS0Assign
sc5000DS0Assign.description: One Octet per DS0. Values are as follows: 1 = Highway 2 = Cascade 3 = Busy Out 4 = Not Present

sc5000ConfigCSUMode.name: sc5000ConfigCSUMode
sc5000ConfigCSUMode.description: 'csuMode' indicates the unit is operating as a T1 channel service unit with the payload from the network interface connected to the payload of the cascade interface. 'concentratorMode' indicates the unit is operating as a T1 channel service unit with the T1 payloads groomed to cross connect within the shelf and the network and cascade interfaces.

sc5000CircuitTable.name: sc5000CircuitTable
sc5000CircuitTable.description: A table that contains information about sc5000 circuits.

sc5000CircuitEntry.name: sc5000CircuitEntry
sc5000CircuitEntry.description: A list of information for each node in the system.

sc5000CircuitIndex.name: sc5000CircuitIndex
sc5000CircuitIndex.description: Integer value which uniquely identifies the node to which this entry is applicable. SCinstance is defined to be ssllddcc where: ss (byte value) - physical shelf slot location (01-32) ll (byte value) - line number (01-128) dd (byte value) - drop number (00-31) cc (byte value) - channel or extension number

sc5000CircuitType.name: sc5000CircuitType
sc5000CircuitType.description: This object defines the circuit type.
